# Workload Identity (SPIFFE, SPIRE, Cloud IAM Federation)

**Audience:** engineers designing or operating service-to-service authentication for Kubernetes, multi-cloud, or AI-agent platforms.

**Scope:** the *infrastructure* layer of identity - "is this workload allowed to call that workload?" For the *application* layer ("is this app/agent allowed to call that app on behalf of this user?") see the Okta XAA / ID-JAG section in `317-okta.mdc`.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> This rule complements:
>
> - `316-zero-trust.mdc` - principles (always-on)
> - `315-iam.mdc` - protocol reference (OIDC/SAML/PKCE/PKI)
> - `412-aws-iam.mdc` - AWS IAM specifics (IRSA, Pod Identity, VPC Lattice)
