## OIDC bridge to cloud IAM

JWT-SVIDs + the SPIRE OIDC Discovery Provider let a workload trade a SPIFFE identity for cloud creds with no static cloud key.

```mermaid
flowchart LR
    wl[Workload] -->|"Workload API"| api[SPIRE Workload API]
    api -->|"JWT-SVID"| oidc["SPIRE OIDC Discovery Provider<br/>(.well-known/openid-configuration)"]
    oidc -->|"AssumeRoleWithWebIdentity"| sts[AWS STS]
    oidc -->|"Workload Identity Federation"| gcpfed[GCP STS]
    oidc -->|"Federated credentials"| azfed[Azure AD]
    oidc -->|"JWT auth method"| vault[HashiCorp Vault]
    sts --> awscreds[Temp AWS creds]
    gcpfed --> gcpcreds[GCP access token]
    azfed --> azcreds[Azure AD token]
    vault --> vtok[Vault token]
```

This collapses "how do I give my pods cloud access" from "distribute IAM keys" to "trust my SPIFFE trust domain as an OIDC issuer."

