## Quick reference cheat sheet

| Designing... | Start with... |
|---|---|
| Service-to-service auth in Kubernetes | SPIFFE + SPIRE + mTLS (Istio/Envoy SDS) |
| Eliminating static cloud IAM keys for workloads | JWT-SVID + cloud OIDC federation |
| Agent calling internal services | SPIFFE SVID for the agent pod |
| AWS workload calling AWS workload | VPC Lattice + `AWS_IAM` + SigV4 |
| GCP workload calling GCP workload | Workload Identity + Cloud Run/Endpoints with IAM |
| Azure workload calling Azure workload | Managed Identity + APIM/Private Link |
| Multi-cloud service identity | SPIFFE federation |
| Single-cloud platform with strong IAM culture | Cloud-native (Lattice / IAM) + XAA at app layer |
| Multi-cloud or k8s-heavy platform | SPIFFE for infra + XAA at app layer |
| Agent calling SaaS on user's behalf | XAA / ID-JAG via Okta (see `317-okta.mdc`) |
| Cross-org agent access | Not yet standardized; interim per-tenant OAuth apps with short TTL |
| Internet machine callers into AWS | Cloudflare Access service auth tokens at the edge |

