## Reviewer Checklist

Identity model:

- [ ] Choice between SPIFFE and cloud IAM is documented with rationale (multi-cloud? attestation granularity? ops capacity?)
- [ ] Trust domain(s) chosen per environment; not shared across envs
- [ ] No long-lived workload secrets introduced

SPIFFE / SPIRE:

- [ ] SPIRE Server in HA with SQL datastore
- [ ] Upstream Authority configured (Vault PKI / AWS PCA / Google CAS / cert-manager)
- [ ] Node attestor uses cloud IID / k8s PSAT (not bare join tokens in prod)
- [ ] Workload attestor includes container image digest where available
- [ ] X.509-SVID TTL ≤ 1h; renewal at ≤ 50% TTL
- [ ] JWT-SVID TTL in minutes; audience required
- [ ] Federation bundles documented if cross-trust-domain
- [ ] mTLS coverage SLO defined and tracked

Cloud IAM (when used):

- [ ] Workload identity (IRSA / Pod Identity / GCP WI / Managed Identity), not static keys
- [ ] OIDC federation for CI (no long-lived deploy keys)
- [ ] AWS service-to-service via VPC Lattice + `AWS_IAM` + SigV4 where applicable
- [ ] Lattice resource policy explicitly names allowed callers (no wildcards)

Authorization on top of mTLS:

- [ ] Istio AuthorizationPolicy / OPA / Envoy ext_authz applied
- [ ] Default-deny posture; explicit allow lists per service
- [ ] SPIFFE ID extracted from URI SAN, not CN

Audit:

- [ ] SPIRE Server audit log streamed to SIEM
- [ ] mTLS handshake failures alerted
- [ ] Registration changes (entry create/update/delete) audited

